The paper deals with the complexity of the MAXIMUM CLIQUE problem in various classes of graphs, specifically multiple interval graphs. This problem is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of graph theory and combinatorics, which are covered in the categories of computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of approximation algorithms, which falls under the category of game theory and economics (cs.GT).
